--- title: Tokens --- # Tokens Pathogen currently exposes Tailwind-compatible `primary-*` and `neutral-*` colour
aliases. Components should move toward semantic roles on top of those aliases so implementation code describes intent
instead of choosing raw colour stops. ## Existing Theme Contract - `--font-sans` is Inter-first: `"Inter", "Avenir
Next", "Segoe UI", -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif`. - `--font-mono` is a standard UI monospace stack. -
`--color-primary-*` defaults to Tailwind blue. - `--color-neutral-*` defaults to Tailwind slate. - Host apps may
override `--color-primary-*`. ## Recommended Semantic Colour Roles ```css :root { --pvc-color-surface:
var(--color-white); --pvc-color-surface-muted: var(--color-neutral-50); --pvc-color-surface-raised: var(--color-white);
--pvc-color-border: var(--color-neutral-200); --pvc-color-border-strong: var(--color-neutral-300); --pvc-color-text:
var(--color-neutral-900); --pvc-color-text-muted: var(--color-neutral-600); --pvc-color-accent:
var(--color-primary-600); --pvc-color-accent-strong: var(--color-primary-700); --pvc-color-danger: var(--color-red-600);
--pvc-color-success: var(--color-emerald-600); --pvc-color-warning: var(--color-amber-600); --pvc-color-focus:
var(--color-primary-500); } ``` ```css .dark { --pvc-color-surface: var(--color-neutral-900); --pvc-color-surface-muted:
var(--color-neutral-800); --pvc-color-surface-raised: color-mix(in oklab, var(--color-neutral-800) 82%, white);
--pvc-color-border: var(--color-neutral-700); --pvc-color-border-strong: var(--color-neutral-600); --pvc-color-text:
var(--color-neutral-100); --pvc-color-text-muted: var(--color-neutral-400); --pvc-color-accent:
var(--color-primary-400); --pvc-color-accent-strong: var(--color-primary-300); --pvc-color-danger: var(--color-red-400);
--pvc-color-success: var(--color-emerald-400); --pvc-color-warning: var(--color-amber-400); --pvc-color-focus:
var(--color-primary-400); } ``` ## Type Scale Use ```css --type-meta: 0.75rem; /* 12px: metadata, hints */
--type-control: 0.875rem; /* 14px: controls, labels, dense UI */ --type-body: 1rem; /* 16px: body copy */
--type-section: 1.25rem; /* 20px: section headings */ --type-page: 1.9375rem; /* 31px: page headings */ ``` Use `14px`
and `16px` as the product workhorses. Use larger sizes sparingly in real application surfaces. ## Radius ```css
--pvc-radius-control-sm: 0.25rem; /* form primitives */ --pvc-radius-control: 0.375rem; /* compact controls */
--pvc-radius-action: 0.5rem; /* buttons, tabs, grouped controls */ --pvc-radius-panel: 0.5rem; /* data grids and panels
*/ ``` Guidance: - Form primitives: `2px` to `4px`. - Buttons, tabs, links focus shapes, and inputs: `6px` to `8px`. -
Data grids and grouped component frames: `8px`. - Large preview and docs containers should avoid `xl` and `2xl` unless
intentionally emphasized. ## Elevation ```css --pvc-shadow-none: none; --pvc-shadow-overlay: 0 1px 3px oklch(0 0 0 /
0.2); ``` Guidance: - Base product surfaces: no shadow. - Grouped surfaces: border plus subtle background difference. -
Overlays, tooltips, popovers, and menus: small shadow. - Avoid `shadow-lg` in product examples. ## Motion ```css
--pvc-duration-fast: 120ms; --pvc-duration-default: 160ms; --pvc-duration-overlay: 200ms; ``` Use colour, border,
background, and opacity transitions before movement. Reserve scale/fade for overlays.
